76561198076678962,Recommended,465780,24682587,"Posted: 2 August, 2016",all,Zeno Spinoza,"This is truly an incredible experience.  I can't help but smile when entering this virtual space. Yes, there are a few quirks here and there regarding a few emulations (I can't seem the get the ""game boys"" to work, and the snes plays great, but it does sound off), but I can start up the 1989 Batman, then decide to walk in the other room to play some Super Mario World, or air hockey while Army of Darkness plays next to it. Then, when I'm bored with that, walk back into the screening room to finish Batman, which I left running. And the atmosphere, and stock games alone are worth the price.I understand this as a total passion project for the developers, and I have no doubt they'll tie up the few loose ends in no time. However, those who're expecting to play two player roms online should probably forget about that. The developers gave us bowling, air hockey, hoop shot, whack-a-mole, and skeeball to play with friends. I haven't tried 2-player yet, so I don't know if others can see your emulations running, but all I hope for is to have friends cheer/tease me while they watch me play Ms Pacman.I would love the tapes to be able to hold entire albums instead of just one song; and I'd love some cheesy, cliche bowling alley animatics when someone gets a strike, or spare, or gutterball, etc.Edit:""Game boys"" are working perfectly now! This game has an incredibly responsive development team! One thing to note further for potential buyers though, I've only been able to get the cabinet arcade games to play 80s arcade games, or prior (basically Golden Axe (1989) is the newest game I've been able to run through MAME on them). Don't expect to play Marvel vs Capcom just yet. However, you can run the SNES emulator on the cabinets, so I can still play TMNT: Turtles in Time, and NBA Jam, but it just doesn't have the same feel. By that, I mean it always saves, and picks up right where I left off. It doesn't do that with the MAME games. That's an incredible feature for typical SNES games, but I'd like the option to reset so it feels like I'm walking in on a new day of arcade action when I re-enter the game.Guys, despite my criticisms, I've never been happier buying a game before. This game deserves more love, and attention."
