,Recommended,465780,29096082,Posted: 7 January,all,Nax_o,"Hard not to recommend this _software_. Just how many competitors are there anywhere? Anarchy Arcade? Why yes, the dev of that software seems to be actually a fan of this project so...Well on to it. Why should you get this? Ask rather why should you not get it. If MAME or Emulation does not ring any bells to you then you should probably skip this. If you however have a decent collection of MAME roms, SNES or Gameboy roms then oh my this game will really bring those roms to life by giving you a virtual playground where to mess around with them. Sega Megadrive does not work at this time so check what it supports if you have exotic emulation tastes.So let's do a short Pro's and Con's list.Pro's+ Being there feeling can't get any closer. Just use the lovely 3rd party software ArcadeManager to make attract videos for your cabinets and presto. The racket, the chatter and general noise is just like the real deal was in the past.+ Did i mention the immersion? It really is the number #1 here. Good (customizable) soundtracks too.+ Awesome _software_ for the person who wants to take their arcade experience to the next level.And the really important Con's- No ROMs included. If you don't at this point understand what i mean by this then you REALLY need to skip this.- Limited multiplay. Others can't play your ROMs so multiplayer is just messing around playing the non ROM related games that can be found at this time.  There is no video streaming or anything like that.- Some people do seem to be confused what this program actually is. I say it straight that this is a _software_ , a glorious front-end for your ROM's.- _This is not a game where you get to play real, licensed old games in a awesome virtual arcade_+- Some people might think the common area games are enough to warrant a buy. I disagree. Bowling, darts, some ball throwing games plus other misc activities where you can mess around with your environment. As fun as they are they are not good enough to warrant a buy alone and this purchase is not exactly cheap so that's a No. Don't buy this game just for the vanilla experience. This one requires you to modify it to your tastes.So with further ado i fully recommend this to people who are fans of old arcades and are in some way active in the scene. The rest be advised of the important con's i listed above."
