etch and sketch to name some!The Community alone and it's  Staff are super helpful and  kind in the community hub and they seem to listen to it's  fans which is a wonderful thing unlike  most  these  days...This Game  shines  most for  it's  Emulators and Rom Support  it's like a  library of you're  favorite  games  but the  way it's done when you  manage to  get it  working  and  have all the  neat cabinet art or  even cartridges that the community  ethier  made by scratch or tributed or get their attract  screens from them it  really  shows  what it's cappable of and  shows how alive and  accurate of an Arcade it  truly is!Last the latest update  if you have  2 or  more  controllers  you'll be happy to know they have  added Local  multiplayer  so  playing 4 player Arcade Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles   side by side  can be a  reality again or  doing co-op Donkey Kong Country is  possible and  they intend to  add more like  Light gun game support!Cons:Of course  there are  some  negatives to the  program but they are not entirely game breaking ethier...Online Support is  a  thing in fact it  can go up to  6 people! but the reason this is  in the  cons area is  because it's not for the  Arcade machines or the Gameboy like handhelds lying around or the Super Nintendo like system in the rec room... It's  for  the  other  games like  Ski Ball,Darts,Hoops  there are two  kinds of  arcade machines by  Digital Cyber  Cherries  themselves one  which is a  6 player like Doom-Goldeneye hybrid and  then a  Zombie lightgun arcade machine which could  be  considered  a  testing  ground for  when real Lightgun support  is  possibleLack of  Customizations in some area's some  people  want to  modify the magazines  and  change the  Arcade  Machines  layouts  more or  even  make there own Arcade  room from scratch in the editor to name some...  There's  more  but those  are the  main I see a lot  mentioned  in terms of  customizing...personally I  want  that  but also would like to 