,Recommended,465780,24717804,"Posted: 4 August, 2016",all,Trigger_Trim,"UPDATE:I am updating my review because in the past week and a half I've seen the developers be very active with the community making a real effort to fix many of the problems with the initial release of this game.  At this point, many of my complaints have been addressed.  There are still issues I am waiting to be fixed, but I am confident that these will be fixed soon and at this point this has become the nostalgic dream I've really been waiting for so long!  Vive controls and positioning is still needing to be fixed, and we still really need to have attract screens with sound running on the arcades.  Shared video streams from friends arcades is still desperately desired.  Otherwise, if you want to feel like you are back in the 80's hanging out in your favorite arcade, this is the way to do it!  I wouldn't hesitate to purchase this game./END UPDATEI was really hoping I would enjoy the arcade machines in this, but the selection of roms that actually work without crashing the program seems very slim.  The default arcade that you get has only 3 functioning games, the rest are all dummy machines with a static image on them and no games.  The complete garbage of the throw in carnival games don't make up for the lack of arcade games.  Many of these add in ""chuck-e-cheese"" type games have already been done in other VR games, and have been done so much better.--The Good--The visuals (after you figure out how to set the resolution in the settings) look pretty good.  The textures and the models of the arcade cabinets and other elements in the environment look very nice.It is possible to get mame hooked up to some of these arcade machines and load your own roms.  It's a big guessing game as to where your configured arcade machines will be located, and then it's an excersize in frustration when you go in to try your new mame rom and get to experience a crash to desktop when all of your favorite roms just don't work.--The Bad--Vive controllers for arcade game play absolutely sucks! input recognition on the touch pad is nowhere near good enough for fast arcade input.The carnival games:I decided to give some of the novelty games a go, since the vive controller input on those should be more natural for things like the light gun game, the punching bag, whack-a-mole etc.Punching bag game. what the heck? You don't even punch the thing! The only interaction I could get to work on the punching bag was to hover my vive controller inside the bag until it outlined in white, then pull the trigger. that seemed to ""punch"" it. that has got to be the stupidest thing I've ever seen.Whack-a-mole:First off, everytime i pick something up, it seems like it goes to the wrong hand, and even sometimes it picks up the completely wrong item. I tried to pick up the mallet on the right hand machine, with my right hand. It grabbed the mallet from the left hand machine (starting the left machine game) and put the mallet into my left hand. that's all sorts of screwed up. But ok, I'm in room scale, I'll just step over there to that machine. Most of my hits wouldn't register. Seemed like the very middle dinosaur just wouldn't register a hit no matter what. I gave up.Zombie Light Gun game:Then I went to play the zombie light gun game. This time the gun went into my correct hand, but what the heck is up with the reload function? I figured out that pressing on the touch pad button was reload (which is stupid, most light gun games I remember as a kid required you to simply shoot off screen to reload). But sometimes pressing the touch pad button actually shoots the gun. I couldn't ever really figure out where it wanted me to press to actually reload. so I got mad and quit.Skee-ball:it's like the skee balls have little jet engines in them and no matter how lightly you toss them, they go launching like they've been shot out of a canon.I know they are working on all of these bugs, but my goodness, this initial impression has made me wonder what in the world happened between the free version they made prior to this and the demo, and this release?  This feels like a rushed out half finished, mostly broken piece of junk to me. I hope this gets fixed soon.I'm still very anxious for this to work like the free version and the demo did. this has been my most anticipated game since the free version on the DK2."
